cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper is about sentiment analysis using word embeddings, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning algorithms for learning word embeddings and classification accuracy, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimization problems, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with text corpora, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves experiments on real-world datasets, which could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision) as sentiment analysis is often used in image and video analysis.
